title: Potato Salad
creator: Nancy Smith
ingredients:
• 5 lb. small red potatoes, boiled with skins & quartered when cool
  • 3 or 4 stalks of celery
  • 4 hard boiled eggs
  • 3 or 4 small pickles
  • 2 c. mayo
  • 1/4 c. pickle juice

title: Peanut Butter Pie
creator: Nancy Smith
ingredients:
• 3 oz. softened neufachtel cheese
  • 1/2 c. smooth peanut butter
  • 1 c. powdered sugar
  • 1/2 c. milk
  • 8 oz. frozen cool whip thawed
  • 1 graham or choc. crust
instructions: Combine Cr. cheese, PB, sugar & milk. Beat until smooth. Gently fold in whipped topping. Freeze 4-6 hrs. Thaw 10 minutes before serving. Top w/ Mrs. Richardson's Hot Fudge Sauce.
description: A recipe for peanut butter pie

title: Beef Barbecue
creator: Nancy Smith
ingredients:
• 4 lb. beef chuck
  • 24 oz. bottle ketchup (2 cups)
  • 1/2 c. vinegar
  • 2 T. Worchestershire sauce
  • 1 large onion
  • 2 Bay leaves
    • <2 C. water
  • S & P
  • 2 T. Br. Sugar
  • 1 T. dry mustard
instructions: Simmer together several hours until meat falls apart. Serve on hamb. buns.
